        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 8:01PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 800 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Mocksville, or 5 miles southeast of Courtney, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bermuda Run, Farmington, and Advance.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
